Buffing up all newbies she meets?<br>
Running so fast and looking so pretty,<br>
Everyone knows Tippwindy!&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Ah....memories....<br>
<br>
When I first started <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>EverQuest</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Balanz, son of Anz</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The seventh son, Brell blessed, but with no inheritance, I took up arms in the name of the All-Father, Lord of the Earth.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Brell</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> made dwarves first among the races below, and tests them constantly like fine steel.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Brell</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> grants us the strength to protect the innocent from evil, and the wisdom to tell between the two.  I was an enthusiast follower of his greatest commandment: to acquire as many gems and precious metals, to take them from the surface world, and return them <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Down Below</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, from whence they were stolen.  Thus, I became known as the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Paladin-Merchant of Kaladim</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I was suprised however to see how well the surface dwellers made good use of the gift of earth that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Brell</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> gave the world, to see the trees and flowers that grew from the soil, and the animals that fed upon the plants, and each other, and the variety of the world.  Thus I found myself a new family, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The Chosen of Tunare</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, who had among their numbers many druids and rangers.<br>
<br>
It was there I first learned of the power and the glory that is mage.<br>
<br>
My guildmate, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Teker Magikos</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, invited me to hunt with him in the watery depths of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kedge Keep</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I remember how impressed I was with his bag of tricks: summoned waterstones to breath beneath the waves, a necklace to see in total darkness, bandages, food, water, and of course, the mighty <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Gobaner</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The scaled denizens occupying the ruins of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kedge</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> stood no chance against the combined might of the three of us.<br>
<br>
Thus, when I was asked to serve refreshments at the wedding of a real life friend on another server that I create my first pure caster, the mage known as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Razamatazz</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  So many of my real life friends were there on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Xev</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that I made it my new home, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ancient Fellowship</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> my new family.<br>
<br>
As best as I recall, that would indeed be a mithril breastplace, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ghoulbane, Greaves of Ro</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->; I also own a mithril two-hander.  All earned the old fashioned way, camping <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Greater FayMart</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for hours on end, buying low, and selling fair.<br>
<br>
You can see <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Teker Magikos</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on the left.<br>
<br>
As for melee, it was actually my paladin-bred fondness for standing toe-to-toe with the enemy that I found resonated so well with being a mage. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Gobaner</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> kicks butt and takes names.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
but originally,<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Balanz, son of Anz, Paladin-Merchant of Kaladim</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
